<h3>Evaluate Your Coverage</h3>
<p>Start by reviewing your current insurance policy. Ensure that you are not over-insured for your needs. You might find options you don’t really need. For example, if your car is older, it may not be worth carrying comprehensive coverage. On the other hand, if you have a newer, more valuable car, maintaining full coverage might be a better option.</p>
