<p>One of the best ways to lower your car insurance premiums is to shop around. Different insurance companies offer different rates for similar coverage. Make sure to get quotes from several providers. You can easily compare premiums online. Look for discounts as well, as many companies offer them for safe driving, good student records, and multiple policies.</p>
<h3>Increase Your Deductible</h3>
<p>Raising your deductible can lead to lower monthly premiums. A deductible is the amount you’ll pay out-of-pocket before your insurance kicks in. Keep in mind that while this can save money on premiums, make sure you have enough savings set aside to cover the deductible if you ever need to file a claim.</p>
