<p>If your car is older or has a low market value, it may be wise to drop collision and comprehensive coverage. After evaluating the actual cash value of your vehicle, determine whether or not the cost of these coverages is justified. You might find savings by reducing coverage on vehicles that may not be worth the investment.</p>
<h3>Review Your Policy Annually</h3>
<p>Insurance needs change, and an annual review of your policy can help ensure you’re not paying too much. Life changes, like moving, changing jobs, or even a new vehicle purchase, may lead to new discounts. Regularly updating your insurer about these changes is necessary for maintaining the best possible rate.</p>
